javax.microedition.lcdui.game

Class GameCanvas

  • java.lang.Object
    • View
      • javax.microedition.lcdui.Canvas
        • javax.microedition.lcdui.game.GameCanvas

  • public abstract class GameCanvas
extends Canvas
    The GameCanvas class extends the Canvas class to provide a framework for creating games. It includes constants representing various key press states that can be used to handle user input in a game. Constants: - DOWN_PRESSED: Represents the down key being pressed. - FIRE_PRESSED: Represents the fire key being pressed. - GAME_A_PRESSED: Represents the game A key being pressed. - GAME_B_PRESSED: Represents the game B key being pressed. - GAME_C_PRESSED: Represents the game C key being pressed. - GAME_D_PRESSED: Represents the game D key being pressed. - LEFT_PRESSED: Represents the left key being pressed. - RIGHT_PRESSED: Represents the right key being pressed. - UP_PRESSED: Represents the up key being pressed. Constructor: - GameCanvas(Context context, AttributeSet attrs): Initializes a new instance of the GameCanvas class with the specified context and attribute set. Methods: - paint(Graphics g): An overridden method from the Canvas class that is used to render the game graphics. This method should be implemented by subclasses to provide custom painting logic.
